{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"readonly","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds","text":"MLNCoordinateBounds","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@MLNCoordinateBounds"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This property contains the smallest rectangle that completely encompasses the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"overlay. Implementers of this protocol must set this area when implementing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their overlay class, and after setting it, you must not change it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If this overlay spans the antimeridian, its bounds may extend west of −180 degrees"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"longitude or east of 180 degrees longitude. For example, an overlay covering the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Pacific Ocean from Tokyo to San Francisco might have a bounds extending"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from (35.68476, −220.24257) to (37.78428, −122.41310)."}]}]}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"property","title":"overlayBounds","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"c:objc(pl)MLNOverlay(py)overlayBounds","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"